<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,152,179]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[755,860,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[755,772,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[785,860,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 16–17. Dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme 1/2 as long as basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme. Cibarial, medial sensilla approximately 6 per side; posterior sensilla 3–4 per side. All tarsi with gray tarsomere V; all tarsomere Is slightly longer than 3 succeeding tarsomeres together.
</paragraph>
