<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,657,683]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[589,696,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[589,606,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[621,696,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the apically blunt posterior postgonite on the right side of aedeagal sheath and the long, broad, sinuated lateral lobe on the left side, but can be distinguished from it by the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
